  "text": "The LLVM loop vectorization infrastructure is composed of the following key components:\n\n1. **LoopVectorizePass** (llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/LoopVectorize.cpp, llvm/include/llvm/Transforms/Vectorize/LoopVectorize.h): The main pass implementation that drives the entire vectorization process. This pass coordinates the legality checks, cost analysis, and vectorization planning.\n\n2. **LoopVectorizeOptions** (llvm/include/llvm/Transforms/Vectorize/LoopVectorize.h): A struct that defines options for the LoopVectorizePass, including flags for controlling when interleaving and vectorization should be applied (InterleaveOnlyWhenForced and VectorizeOnlyWhenForced).\n\n3. **LoopVectorizationLegality** (llvm/include/llvm/Transforms/Vectorize/LoopVectorizationLegality.h, llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/LoopVectorizationLegality.cpp): A unit that checks whether it is legal to vectorize a loop. It performs memory checks and scalar checks, ensuring that vectorization will not change program correctness.\n\n4. **LoopVectorizationCostModel** (llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/LoopVectorize.cpp): A class that determines the profitability of vectorization by analyzing instruction costs using the TargetTransformInfo. It decides on optimal vector widths and unroll factors based on cost analysis.\n\n5. **VPlan** (llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/VPlan.h, llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/VPlan.cpp): The Vectorization Plan data structure that represents the vectorized loop body in a target-independent form. VPlan models the complete vector loop and vectorization skeleton, supporting both fixed-width and scalable vectorization. The header VPlan.h is a private header located in the implementation directory rather than the public includes directory."
}

